11/01/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Turkish government announced late on Thursday (January 8th) it had appointed Egemen Bagis as its new chief negotiator with the EU.
Bagis is an adviser of Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on foreign affairs and deputy chairman of the ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP).
He will replace Foreign Minister Ali Babacan as the chief negotiator.
On Friday, the Czech presidency of the EU welcomed the appointment, saying it is "a good step not only for Turkey, but also for the EU".
(Anadolu news agency, Hurriyet, Reuters, Xinhua - 09/01/09)
